com.anggrayudi.hiddenapi

Class InternalAccessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.anggrayudi.hiddenapi.InternalAccessor

  • public final class InternalAccessor
extends java.lang.Object
    Created by Anggrayudi on 11/03/2016.

    A utility class that provides access to all resources in com.android.internal.R class.

    If you want to retrieve the same value again, don't get it by using this utility class. Save to ResourcesHolder instead. Also, you can send ResourcesHolder class object to another class via: Intent.putExtra(String key, ResourcesHolder instance) to avoid re-reflection to the same value.

    You can find which resources are available for current API level. See:

    • R_10 - for API 10
    • R_16 - for API 16
    • R_17 - for API 17
    • R_21 - for API 21
    • R_22 - for API 22

      • getResourceId

        public static int getResourceId(java.lang.String clas,
                java.lang.String resName)
                         throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException,
                                ResourceNotFoundException
        Pick resource id from com.android.internal.R via reflection.
        Parameters:
        clas - for example = string, drawable, color, style, id, attr. And they will be wrote as com.android.internal.R.drawable
        resName - for example = cancel, ic_launcher, activity_main
        Returns:
        internal resource id in integer, for example: com.android.internal.R.xml.audio_assets returns 17891329 in integer.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        ResourceNotFoundException
